The remains of the former Governor of Lagos State, Lateef Jakande has been laid to rest.  The burial prayers is taking place at his residence. Deputy Governor of Lagos state, Dr Obafemi Hamzat, former Ogun State Governor Ibikunle Amosun and sons of the deceased, Deji and Seyi Jakande took the front row. Earlier, Amosun was spotted signing the condolence register. More Photos; Former Lagos Governor, Alhaji Lateef Jakande, is dead. He died on Thursday morning in Lagos at 91. He was a former journalist who became governor of Lagos State from 1979 to 1983. He later emerged Minister of Works under the Sani Abacha military regime (1993–98). details shortly… In "Politics" Veteran journalist and former Lagos State Governor Lateef Jakande passed on Thursday. Deputy Editor EMMANUEL OLADESU writes on the life and times of the ‘Action Governor,’ his legacies and lessons for the political classNobody will live forever. But, history will be kind to mortars who left good legacies in their… In "Opinion" Bolaji Buhari Lagos - A former Deputy Governor of Lagos State, Alhaja Sinatu Ojikutu, has congratulated the first civilian Governor of the state, Alhaji Lateef Jakande, who attained the age of 91 on Thursday. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that Jakande governed Lagos State from 1979-1983. In a… In "Politics"